<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1997-02-28</DATELINE><TITLE>Problems and prospects of developing effective therapy for common cold viruses</TITLE><BODY>No effective treatment for common colds has yet been developed. Combination antiviral and anti-inflammatory therapies are the best hope for intervention after the onset of symptoms. Prophylaxis, especially in the form of vaccination, would have a major impact in disease prevention. These approaches offer new avenues for treating populations at risk and are of particular significance to those with asthma or chronic bronchitis.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>